## PRE-STEP 1 — Classify and Normalise

| Format received | Type | Action |
|---|---|---|
| 9 digits starting with `2xx` | `fixed_geographic` | Prepend `351` ? 12 digits |
| 9 digits starting with `9xx` | `mobile` | Prepend `351` ? 12 digits |
| 12 digits starting with `49x` | `iot_m2m` | Prepend `351` ? 15 digits |
| 15 digits starting with `35149` | `iot_m2m` | Already normalised |
| `800` / `808` / `707` / `760` / `761` | `special` | Use as is |
| `300` to `309` | `non_geographic_ip` | Use as is |
| Any other format | `INVALID` | Inform user and **stop** |

`fixed_geographic` subtypes:
`21x` Lisbon · `22x` Porto · `23x–28x` Regions · `291` Madeira · `292/295/296` Azores

`mobile` subtypes (origin prefix — does NOT determine current operator):
`91x` Vodafone · `92x` NOS · `93x` NOS · `95x` NOS additional · `96x` MEO

