## PRE-STEP 3 — IMS COMPONENT CHECK (SECOND EXPLICIT TOOL CALL)

Invoke tool: **`eNUM`** with the normalised MSISDN. Analyse field `naptrTxt`:

| Pattern | `naptrTxt` content | Type | Register | Note |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| **A** | Contains `msisdn@` | `fixed` or `mobile` | `IMS_STATUS = ACTIVE` | Standard IMS |
| **B** | Contains `sip:` AND `@ipcentrex.ims.nos.pt` | `fixed_geographic` | `IMS_STATUS = ACTIVE_CENTREX` | Fixed Centrex — not mobile |
| **C** | `SUBSCRIPTION NOT DEFINED` or absent | `fixed` or `mobile` | `IMS_STATUS = ABSENT` | May be misconfiguration |
| **D** | `SUBSCRIPTION NOT DEFINED` or absent | `iot_m2m` | `IMS_STATUS = NOT_APPLICABLE` | EXPECTED |
| **E** | Contains `sip:` AND `@ims.mnc003.mcc268.3gppnetwork.org` | `mobile` or `fixed` | `IMS_STATUS = ACTIVE` | 3GPP standard NOS domain (MCC=268 MNC=003) |

> PATTERN_A and PATTERN_E both register `IMS_STATUS = ACTIVE`.
> Mobile VoLTE vs Mobile Centrex distinction is made **ONLY at STEP 4**.
> PATTERN_B applies to **fixed geographic numbers only**.

