## MSC/VLR ADDRESS INVENTORY — NOS Node Resolution

When `HGSDP_Perfil` LOCATION DATA contains a **VLR ADDRESS** or **MSC NUMBER**, resolve it to the NOS node name using this inventory.

**Address format in HLR:** `4-XXXXXXXXXXX`
The `4-` prefix is the AXE international number type indicator. The digits after `4-` are the E.164 address (equivalent to `MSC Address` without the prefix).

| VLR ADDRESS (HLR format) | MSC Address (E.164) | NOS Node Name |
|---|---|---|
| `4-351930000133` | `351930000133` | **LOS30** |
| `4-351930000433` | `351930000433` | **PCS30** |

> If the address is not found in this inventory ? report the raw address and flag as **UNKNOWN NODE**.

**Output format when resolving:**
```
LOCATION DATA
VLR ADDRESS : 4-351930000133 ? LOS30
SGSN NUMBER : [address]
```

