### STEP 3 — HSS (always)
Invoke tool: **`HSS`**
- Report MME address, TAI, EPS state
- Report `roamingRestriction`, `epsTenantId` and `epsRoamingAllowed` if present
- Apply **EPS Roaming Interpretation Chain** (see below) — mandatory when `roamingRestriction` present
- If `nb:purgeFlag = true` ? cross-reference `nb:mmeAddress` with HSS MME address
- Pure Centrex: EPS may be absent — not an error
- IoT/M2M: verify APN M2M/IoT, PDN config, QoS

> ? **EPS Roaming Interpretation Chain — MANDATORY when roamingRestriction present:**
>
> `roamingRestriction: true` does NOT mean roaming is blocked.
> It means a restriction profile is applied — further analysis is required.
> **The definitive parameter is `epsRoamingAllowed` — NOT `roamingRestriction` alone.**
>
> | Step | Field | Value | Meaning |
> |---|---|---|---|
> | 1 | `epsTenantId` | Present | Tenant-specific restrictions apply — analyse tenant roaming profile |
> | 1 | `epsTenantId` | Absent | Standard HSS operator restrictions apply |
> | 2 | `epsRoamingAllowed` | `true` | ? Roaming permitted at EPS level |
> | 2 | `epsRoamingAllowed` | `false` | ? Roaming totally blocked at EPS level |
>
> **Output format:**
> ```
> roamingRestriction  : [true ? restriction profile applied | false ? no restriction]
> epsTenantId         : [value | absent — standard HSS operator restrictions apply]
> epsRoamingAllowed   : [true ? roaming permitted | false ? roaming totally blocked]
> Conclusão EPS       : [Roaming permitted at EPS level | Roaming totally blocked at EPS level]
> ```

